+# Security False-Positive Analysis — CVE-2026-48961 (perl, Debian bookworm)
+
+**CVE-2026-48961** — *not-affected*
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|-------|
+| CVE | CVE-2026-48961 |
+| Package | `perl` (bundled `cpan/IO-Compress/bin/zipdetails`) |
+| Distribution | Debian 12 (bookworm) |
+| Shipped version | `5.36.0-7+deb12u3` (IO::Compress 2.106 / zipdetails 2.104) |
+| Verdict | **not-affected** — `unpackValueQ` typo not present |
+| Affected range | IO::Compress **2.207 before 2.220** (zipdetails 4.000–4.005) |
+| Introduced | https://github.com/pmqs/IO-Compress/commit/ddfe67584a228877e5d28840da75ff32e435a5e3 (v2.207) |
+| CWE | CWE-755 |
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+CVE-2026-48961: `zipdetails` calls misspelled `unpackValueQ` (should be
+`unpackValue_Q`) when decoding an 8-byte UID/GID in Info-ZIP ux (0x7875).
+
+## Why bookworm perl is not affected
+
+Bundled IO::Compress is **2.106** / zipdetails **2.104** (before 2.207).
+`decodeLitteEndian()` only handles 4-byte values (`die "unsupported"` otherwise)
+and never calls `unpackValueQ`. Debian already marks bookworm
+`libio-compress-perl` **not-affected** ("Vulnerable code introduced later").
+
+## Verdict
+
+**No code patch required.** See `patches/CVE-2026-48961/README.md`.
+
+## References
+
+- https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-48961
+- https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-48961
+- https://github.com/pmqs/IO-Compress/commit/33c89d03d6e746ed2ead4f2f6570d47864c61bc7
